<!-- The following paragraph has been deleted by a later hand applying a large cross in pencil over the whole paragraph AM -->
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">My dear Sir</p>
<lb/><p><space extent="6" unit="chars"/>Much thanks to you &amp; to 
<lb/>your family. I have received the knife 
<lb/>which you have kindly sent me. 
<lb/>It is the best, useful &amp; most <w>va<seg type="hyphen">-</seg>
<lb break="no"/>luable</w> knife I ever had. I shall
<lb/>take great care of it one would
<lb/>take much interest to see it.
<lb/>I am still at <placeName>Kisulutimi</placeName>. I am going
<lb/>on with the school with few <w>child<seg type="hyphen">-</seg>
<lb break="no"/>ren</w> to which some are added from
<lb/>the rescued slaves. May Heaven
<lb/>conduct and help us in this &amp; this
<lb/>may be the means of bringing the <unclear cert="medium">route</unclear>
<lb/>to the eternal joy.</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><add place="inline" hand="#U" rend="gray">35</add></p>
				
<pb facs="liv_020051_0002" n="0002"/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">I have received the letter from <persName>Dr
<lb/>Foster</persName>. There are much work going on 
<lb/>at <settlement>Frere Town</settlement>. The consul was very -
<lb/>much delighted with the place.</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><persName>Mr Sparshott</persName> will be soon coming.
<lb/>Please to give my best regards to
<lb/><persName>Winifred</persName> &amp; <persName>Claude</persName>. I have a great <w>de<seg type="hyphen">-</seg>
<lb break="no"/>sire</w> to come and see you once more.</p>
<lb/>
<lb/>
<lb/><p rend="right">I remain yours
<lb/><choice><abbr>affec<hi rend="underline">t</hi><!-- .. underneath the underline --></abbr><expan>affectionate</expan></choice> &amp; grateful
<lb/><hi rend="double-underline"><persName>Jacob Wainwright</persName></hi></p>


